==English==

===Noun===

'''sneak'''

#A mean, sneaking fellow.
#A ball bowled so as to roll along the ground; -- called also grub.

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|sneak||}}
<!--Also irregular-->

#To creep or steal (away or about) privately; to come or go meanly, as a person afraid or ashamed to be seen; as, to sneak away from company.
#To hide, esp. in a mean or cowardly manner.

===={{usage}}====
''The past participle "snuck" as come into common usage, by analogy with [[strike]]. This usage was almost unknown at the turn of the twentieth century, but is now acceptable in all but the most formal written English. This is the only irregual verb form to enter the language in several hundred years.''